column25: The annual report is prepared in accordance with the Danish Financial Statements Act.
column26: In our opinion, the financial statements give a true and fair view of the Company's  financial position at 31 December 2017 and of the results of the Company's operations for the financial year 1 January - 31 December 2017.
column29: Other external expenses include expenses related to administration, etc.
column30: Financial income and expenses are recognised in the income statement at the amounts relating to the financial year. Net financials include interest income and expenses, financial expenses relating to finance leases, realised and unrealised capital/exchange gains and losses on securities and foreign currency transactions, amortisation of mortgage loans and surcharges and allowances under the advance-payment-of-tax scheme, etc.
column31: Liabilities, which include trade payables and other payables, are measured at amortised cost, which is usually equivalent to nominal value.
column32: Receivables are measured at amortised cost.
column33: Tax for the year, which comprises the current tax charge for the year and changes in the deferred tax charge, including changes arising from changes in tax rates, is recognised in the income statement as regards the portion that relates to entries directly in equity.
column34: We conducted our audit in accordance with International Standards on Auditing (ISAs) andthe additional requirements applicable in Denmark.
